==Latin==
===Adjective===
'''optimus''' ''m'', '''[[optima]]''' ''f'', '''[[optimum]]''' ''n''

First and second declension

# best; irregular superlative of '''[[bonus]]''', ''good''.
#: ''Hic mundus perfectissimus est etiam mundorum possibilium omnium optimus'' : This most perfect world is even the best of all possible worlds ([[Immanuel Kant]], echoing Leibniz). [http://www.ikp.uni-bonn.de/kant/agb-metaphysica/II2.html]

===Etymology===
From '''[[optare]]''', ''choose'' or ''prefer''

